        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Fig. 6. Morphological characters of Hemicrepidius. H. memnonius: a) Mesothorax, ventral view, b) Crenulate basal carina on elytra (arrow), c) Detail of subumbilicate punctures, lateral edge of pronotum, e) Microserrations on sides of abdominal ventrites, arrow. H. hemipodus: d) Simple basal carina on elytra (arrow)." ;
